	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Doommaster1994</b> [ Mon Aug 01, 2011 1:17 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>How NES Music Was REALLY Composed</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey there, guys,
<br />I have talked to countless NES composers and they have told me how they composed their NES music and I thought I'd share what they said to you guys:
<br />
<br />Akito Nakatsuka - Family BASIC
<br />Alberto Gonzalez - Compact Editor
<br />Allister Brimble - Hex Code, Tracker
<br />Barry Leitch - MODTracker for Commodore Amiga
<br />Brad Fuller - Music V Language
<br />Charles Deenen - Hex Code Written Directly on NES
<br />Dave Warhol - Cakewalk and a program he created that used his own voice patches
<br />Dave Wise - Hex Code
<br />Doug Brandon - CuBase (Atari ST)
<br />Earl Vickers - Music V Language
<br />Ed Bogas - Atari Music Studio
<br />Elliot Delman &amp; Steven Samler - Digital Performer
<br />Frank Klepacki - Dr. T KCS on Commodore Amiga
<br />Gavan Anderson - Hex Code
<br />George Sanger - Digital Performer
<br />Hirohiko Takayama - Assembley Hex Code on MS-DOS
<br />Hirokazu Tanaka - Family BASIC
<br />Jeroen Tel - Hex code with his own program for MS-DOS (He sent me 
<br />some of the original music files!)
<br />Jonathan Dunn - Hex Code.
<br />Kinuyo Yamashita - Hex code.
<br />Koji Kondo - Family BASIC
<br />Mark Cooksey - Hex Code and Converted MIDIs in C-Lab Notator
<br />Mark Knight - CuBase on Atari ST with Silver Box that emulated NES chip.
<br />Mark Van Hecke - Dr. T KCS on Atari ST using FB-01.
<br />Marshall Parker - Hex Code
<br />Neil Baldwin - Hex Code.
<br />Paul Webb - Hex Code
<br />Paul Wilkinson - Cakewalk and Hex Code
<br />Russell Ginns/Michael Artin - Master Tracks Pro
<br />Steven Samler/Elliott Delman - Performer
<br />Tania Smith - Hex Code
<br />Zap Ajisai - Music Maker (MSX)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


